<div type="translation">
<head>Translation</head>
<p>[?The city has honoured] Aur(elius) Gaius, centurio frumentarius, who has conducted himself decently and bravely in the province of Asia, for his goodwill and affection towards her.  The most worthy Ant(onius) Neikomachos oversaw the erection of the statue.</p></div>

<div type="commentary">
<head>Commentary</head>
<p>This inscription is similar to, but not identical with, <xref type="inscription" n="1789" href="120932">12.932</xref> (=CIG 2802). Foer discussion, see <bibl n="cmr1981">Roueché, <title level="j">JRS</title> 71, 1981, 113-117.</bibl></p>
</div>

